Quote: A perfectionist, Dame Rangimarie was considered to be the expert in the field of raranga - weaving raw flax strips into items such as kete and mats - and whatu taniko or finger-weaving fine flax fibre into garments., Whatu taniko, made without the aid of loom or tools, is Te Kanawa's forte.
